WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:07.632 --> 00:00:13.221 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:00:13.304 --> 00:00:16.474 position:50% align:center
[MAC] "As the falling sun began
to dye the wasteland red,

00:00:16.558 --> 00:00:19.811 position:50% align:center
the Nomad happened across
the hummingbird once more,

00:00:19.894 --> 00:00:21.938 position:50% align:center
but the tiny creature
was exhausted

00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:25.859 position:50% align:center
and knew its death was near.

00:00:25.942 --> 00:00:28.445 position:50% align:center
Though the end of his journey
was nowhere in sight,

00:00:28.528 --> 00:00:32.615 position:50% align:center
the Nomad stopped to speak with
the hummingbird one last time."

00:00:32.699 --> 00:00:37.328 position:50% align:center
[CROWD]
Joe! Joe! Joe! Joe...!

00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:40.206 position:50% align:center
[MAC] "'Listen, Hummingbird.
As you've said,

00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:43.501 position:50% align:center
I have eyes to see you,
ears to hear your song,

00:00:43.585 --> 00:00:46.921 position:50% align:center
and a mouth to speak with you.

00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:49.424 position:50% align:center
I have hands to shoo you away,

00:00:49.507 --> 00:00:52.719 position:50% align:center
and I have legs to
carry me on my journey,

00:00:52.802 --> 00:00:57.640 position:50% align:center
but every other thing I had
in this life is gone now.

00:00:57.724 --> 00:01:01.936 position:50% align:center
I have these few things
left and nothing else.'"

00:01:03.605 --> 00:01:05.648 position:50% align:center
[MIGUEL]
..."'and nothing else.'

00:01:05.732 --> 00:01:08.777 position:50% align:center
The hummingbird's voi-voice
had grown weak"...

00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:11.112 position:50% align:center
[MAC] "The hummingbird's
voice had grown weak,

00:01:11.196 --> 00:01:14.324 position:50% align:center
but it answered without the
slightest hint of doubt.

00:01:14.407 --> 00:01:16.451 position:50% align:center
'That is a lie.

00:01:16.534 --> 00:01:19.454 position:50% align:center
You have a past
and its regrets.

00:01:19.537 --> 00:01:22.207 position:50% align:center
A present with the
choices it brings.

00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:25.460 position:50% align:center
And a future that
is undetermined.

00:01:25.543 --> 00:01:27.921 position:50% align:center
To a dying soul like me,

00:01:28.004 --> 00:01:32.801 position:50% align:center
you still seem to have as much
as this world can offer.'

00:01:32.884 --> 00:01:37.764 position:50% align:center
'Yes. I can't deny that.
You've beaten me again.

00:01:37.847 --> 00:01:41.059 position:50% align:center
Please, sing for me.'

00:01:41.142 --> 00:01:43.436 position:50% align:center
The Nomad sat with
the little bird,

00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:49.818 position:50% align:center
awaiting its song once more,
but heard only the wind.

00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:53.571 position:50% align:center
For as the Nomad spoke,
the hummingbird had passed."

00:01:53.655 --> 00:01:55.407 position:50% align:center
[MAYA] And I'm the one
who just let him turn you

00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:57.701 position:50% align:center
into something else!

00:01:57.784 --> 00:02:00.161 position:50% align:center
I felt like I had no
choice but to sign,

00:02:00.245 --> 00:02:03.998 position:50% align:center
or Miguel might never
get his operation!

00:02:04.082 --> 00:02:05.542 position:50% align:center
[SAKUMA]
And I was right.

00:02:05.625 --> 00:02:07.919 position:50% align:center
You're on top of the
Megaloboxing world--

00:02:08.003 --> 00:02:10.213 position:50% align:center
hero to millions!

00:02:10.296 --> 00:02:11.798 position:50% align:center
What is that worth?

00:02:11.881 --> 00:02:15.301 position:50% align:center
You could never have achieved
all this as the man you were.

00:02:26.604 --> 00:02:28.523 position:50% align:center
[SAKUMA] You're not the nobody
looking up at the legend

00:02:28.606 --> 00:02:30.483 position:50% align:center
on the big screen anymore.

00:02:30.567 --> 00:02:33.403 position:50% align:center
Now, you're the one
we look up to.

00:02:37.365 --> 00:02:40.201 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
I'm not your damn hero.

00:04:15.422 --> 00:04:18.383 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
Listen, it's not a normal match.

00:04:18.466 --> 00:04:21.344 position:50% align:center
I won't be training
you to defeat Mac.

00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:24.347 position:50% align:center
Getting you home safely
is my goal here.

00:04:24.431 --> 00:04:26.933 position:50% align:center
I don't wanna see you
trading punches with him.

00:04:27.017 --> 00:04:28.101 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
Got it.

00:04:28.184 --> 00:04:29.894 position:50% align:center
[YURI] This is strictly
a defensive drill.

00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:31.146 position:50% align:center
No counters for now.

00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:33.106 position:50% align:center
You don't want me
attacking at all?

00:04:33.189 --> 00:04:36.276 position:50% align:center
[YURI] A strong enough defense
can break down an opponent.

00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:38.278 position:50% align:center
Fighting without
throwing a punch.

00:04:38.361 --> 00:04:40.321 position:50% align:center
The fundamentals of boxing.

00:04:40.405 --> 00:04:42.449 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
Whatever you say.

00:04:42.532 --> 00:04:44.117 position:50% align:center
Think you can land a hit on me?

00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:46.995 position:50% align:center
A bowl of ramen at First
Star says you can't.

00:04:47.078 --> 00:04:50.248 position:50% align:center
Hope your movement stayed as
sharp as your tongue, Joe.

00:04:50.331 --> 00:04:51.791 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
Begin.

00:04:54.836 --> 00:04:58.256 position:50% align:center
Stay on the move!
Cover the whole ring!

00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:08.183 position:50% align:center
Quite the impressive
piece of work here.

00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.852 position:50% align:center
[OICHO] The heavy leather on
the outside acts like armor,

00:05:10.935 --> 00:05:13.855 position:50% align:center
soaking up a lot of the force
of the opponent's punches.

00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:16.524 position:50% align:center
It was designed really
well for that.

00:05:16.608 --> 00:05:18.943 position:50% align:center
True, it does make
for a strong guard,

00:05:19.027 --> 00:05:20.195 position:50% align:center
but there's a tradeoff.

00:05:20.278 --> 00:05:22.655 position:50% align:center
The arms are ridiculously stiff.

00:05:22.739 --> 00:05:25.158 position:50% align:center
That tough cowhide's a bit
of a double-edged sword.

00:05:25.241 --> 00:05:26.618 position:50% align:center
The other guy's
shots bounce off,

00:05:26.701 --> 00:05:28.745 position:50% align:center
but you can barely throw back.

00:05:28.828 --> 00:05:30.413 position:50% align:center
It wouldn't be a big
problem for Chief

00:05:30.497 --> 00:05:32.123 position:50% align:center
since he was built like a bear,

00:05:32.207 --> 00:05:34.542 position:50% align:center
but I'm thinking Joe
would struggle with it.

00:05:34.626 --> 00:05:35.877 position:50% align:center
Makes sense to me.

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.879 position:50% align:center
So what'll we do?

00:05:40.131 --> 00:05:41.966 position:50% align:center
[SACHIO] We'll strip
it down and rebuild it.

00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:45.970 position:50% align:center
With an expanded range
of motion in the arms.

00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:48.765 position:50% align:center
And I think this'll
help with that.

00:05:48.848 --> 00:05:51.351 position:50% align:center
Deerskin, eh?

00:05:51.434 --> 00:05:53.687 position:50% align:center
Tough, but more
flexible than cowhide.

00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:57.148 position:50% align:center
It can keep up with Joe's
moves while keeping him safe.

00:05:58.858 --> 00:06:00.610 position:50% align:center
That settles it.

00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:11.246 position:50% align:center
Looks like the kid got
somethin' out of his time

00:06:11.329 --> 00:06:13.665 position:50% align:center
in the ring after all, huh?

00:06:16.126 --> 00:06:17.502 position:50% align:center
[OICHO]
And there's nobody alive

00:06:17.585 --> 00:06:21.339 position:50% align:center
who understands the way Joe
fights better than Sachio.

00:06:35.478 --> 00:06:36.980 position:50% align:center
[MIKIO] If you realize
you made a mistake

00:06:37.063 --> 00:06:38.690 position:50% align:center
and stop to change course,

00:06:38.773 --> 00:06:41.151 position:50% align:center
isn't that a step
toward the future?

00:06:41.234 --> 00:06:45.238 position:50% align:center
[siren wailing]

00:06:47.907 --> 00:06:50.035 position:50% align:center
Seems there was a jumper.

00:06:51.327 --> 00:06:54.539 position:50% align:center
"Yet another youth who
surrendered to despair."

00:06:54.622 --> 00:06:56.041 position:50% align:center
What's that nonsense?

00:06:56.124 --> 00:06:57.834 position:50% align:center
If you expect a better future,

00:06:57.917 --> 00:06:59.169 position:50% align:center
you should be willing
to stick around

00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:01.504 position:50% align:center
and help make it a reality.

00:07:01.588 --> 00:07:05.383 position:50% align:center
Is it so wrong
to expect better?

00:07:05.467 --> 00:07:07.260 position:50% align:center
To believe that you can
reach a brighter future

00:07:07.344 --> 00:07:11.181 position:50% align:center
by keeping a positive
attitude and working hard?

00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:14.601 position:50% align:center
Oh, God.

00:07:14.684 --> 00:07:17.520 position:50% align:center
You weren't thinking about
jumping yourself, were you?

00:07:19.314 --> 00:07:21.191 position:50% align:center
No, sir, just
gathering my thoughts

00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:24.027 position:50% align:center
so I could prepare a response
to Professor Shirato.

00:07:24.110 --> 00:07:26.863 position:50% align:center
[SAKUMA]
Right. Yeah, good thinking.

00:07:26.946 --> 00:07:28.281 position:50% align:center
We need to show
that ignorant ass

00:07:28.365 --> 00:07:30.450 position:50% align:center
exactly what he's dealing with.

00:07:30.533 --> 00:07:32.327 position:50% align:center
The march of progress
won't stop.

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:35.872 position:50% align:center
Not for his outmoded ethics,
not for anything.

00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:43.630 position:50% align:center
Question, sir... Do you think
Mac will come back here?

00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:48.343 position:50% align:center
Heh. People are driven
by one of two things:

00:07:48.426 --> 00:07:50.720 position:50% align:center
Pleasure or fear.

00:07:50.804 --> 00:07:52.764 position:50% align:center
Mac lost everything once,

00:07:52.847 --> 00:07:56.976 position:50% align:center
and now, he has so
much more to lose.

00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:59.854 position:50% align:center
Think he's brave enough
to risk it again?

00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:21.501 position:50% align:center
[MIGUEL]
Daddy's gonna come home.

00:08:21.584 --> 00:08:23.336 position:50% align:center
I know he will,
'cause the hummingbird's

00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:25.839 position:50% align:center
gonna show him the way back.

00:08:27.632 --> 00:08:29.300 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:08:29.384 --> 00:08:32.887 position:50% align:center
Now, here. Time to
get you to bed.

00:08:56.703 --> 00:08:59.372 position:50% align:center
Have a drink.

00:08:59.456 --> 00:09:02.542 position:50% align:center
They said they'll be done with
the Gear inspection soon.

00:09:04.169 --> 00:09:05.795 position:50% align:center
That good?

00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:15.680 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much, Maya.

00:09:15.764 --> 00:09:20.352 position:50% align:center
[gasps] And where's this coming
from all of a sudden?

00:09:20.435 --> 00:09:22.395 position:50% align:center
Sakuma's done a lot for me.

00:09:22.479 --> 00:09:26.107 position:50% align:center
He's the only reason
I can still move.

00:09:26.191 --> 00:09:28.860 position:50% align:center
Even got me back
into Megaloboxing.

00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:33.615 position:50% align:center
But on my own, I'm a
body stuck in a bed.

00:09:33.698 --> 00:09:35.700 position:50% align:center
I'm powerless to do
anything myself,

00:09:35.784 --> 00:09:38.203 position:50% align:center
even take a drink of water.

00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:44.876 position:50% align:center
He may have done a lot for me,
but you keep me alive.

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:05.230 position:50% align:center
Doing all right there, friend?

00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:07.857 position:50% align:center
Mind telling me why
you parked here?

00:10:08.858 --> 00:10:13.154 position:50% align:center
I'm not in the mood to talk.
Just lemme sleep.

00:10:19.035 --> 00:10:25.208 position:50% align:center
So is this your car?
License and proof of insurance.

00:10:28.128 --> 00:10:30.088 position:50% align:center
[TANAKA]
That was an order, sir.

00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:33.633 position:50% align:center
Out of the car now!
That was an order!

00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:37.387 position:50% align:center
[HAKEEM] Easy! Don't be one
of those cops, Tanaka.

00:10:37.470 --> 00:10:40.640 position:50% align:center
Sir, he's a
noncompliant suspect.

00:10:40.724 --> 00:10:41.975 position:50% align:center
What do you suspect him of?

00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:45.145 position:50% align:center
Parking his fancy car in
a really sketchy place?

00:10:45.228 --> 00:10:47.772 position:50% align:center
Strange move, but there's
nothin' criminal about that.

00:10:47.856 --> 00:10:49.399 position:50% align:center
Is there?

00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:52.444 position:50% align:center
Uh. Wait, Mac?

00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:58.283 position:50% align:center
What? Bro, it's Hakeem!
What the hell?

00:11:00.326 --> 00:11:01.911 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
Partner?

00:11:18.803 --> 00:11:20.805 position:50% align:center
Hey, thanks, rookie.

00:11:22.265 --> 00:11:26.811 position:50% align:center
[TANAKA] Um, I'm really
sorry about before, sir.

00:11:26.895 --> 00:11:28.730 position:50% align:center
I didn't recognize you.

00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:30.732 position:50% align:center
Nah, kid. You're fine.

00:11:30.815 --> 00:11:33.276 position:50% align:center
I just got a whole lot
goin' on right now.

00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:35.904 position:50% align:center
Tanaka here is a
fellow Megaloboxer,

00:11:35.987 --> 00:11:38.531 position:50% align:center
hopin' to be our next superstar.

00:11:38.615 --> 00:11:39.824 position:50% align:center
Hey, good on ya.

00:11:39.908 --> 00:11:41.326 position:50% align:center
[TANAKA]
I saw the title match.

00:11:41.409 --> 00:11:43.286 position:50% align:center
Sir, you were a beast.

00:11:43.370 --> 00:11:44.621 position:50% align:center
Who woulda thought, right?

00:11:44.704 --> 00:11:46.998 position:50% align:center
Back when you started
showin' up at the gym,

00:11:47.082 --> 00:11:50.126 position:50% align:center
I thought it was cool, gettin'
to practice with a former pro.

00:11:50.210 --> 00:11:54.506 position:50% align:center
I never knew you were
the future champ!

00:11:54.589 --> 00:11:57.300 position:50% align:center
You know what punk-asses
the kids were around here.

00:11:57.384 --> 00:11:58.343 position:50% align:center
Mouthin' off to the cops

00:11:58.426 --> 00:12:00.303 position:50% align:center
is still their favorite
thing to do,

00:12:00.387 --> 00:12:01.596 position:50% align:center
but then I show
'em this picture,

00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:04.432 position:50% align:center
and just like that,
they're puppy dogs.

00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:09.104 position:50% align:center
[TANAKA] Everybody knows
the story of Mac.

00:12:09.187 --> 00:12:10.980 position:50% align:center
The model policeman.

00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:12.774 position:50% align:center
The officer who put his
own life on the line

00:12:12.857 --> 00:12:15.777 position:50% align:center
to save those innocent
children from harm.

00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:16.820 position:50% align:center
[HAKEEM]
That's right.

00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:20.240 position:50% align:center
Mac Rosario, the city's
greatest hero.

00:12:20.323 --> 00:12:22.242 position:50% align:center
I screwed up the "hero" thing.

00:12:22.325 --> 00:12:25.328 position:50% align:center
Coulda gone out on top,
but I survived it.

00:12:26.538 --> 00:12:29.124 position:50% align:center
All right, dude,
what's up with you?

00:12:29.207 --> 00:12:31.960 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
Not a thing.

00:12:32.043 --> 00:12:35.797 position:50% align:center
There hasn't been from
the start. I know that now.

00:12:41.136 --> 00:12:43.013 position:50% align:center
Not sure why you'd say that.

00:12:43.096 --> 00:12:44.597 position:50% align:center
I've spent a whole
lot of time thinkin',

00:12:44.681 --> 00:12:46.349 position:50% align:center
"If it'd been me back there,

00:12:46.433 --> 00:12:50.020 position:50% align:center
could I have taken care of
that situation like Mac?"

00:12:53.815 --> 00:12:57.027 position:50% align:center
If I'm bein' honest, I think
my knees would buckle.

00:12:57.110 --> 00:13:00.363 position:50% align:center
I don't know that I've got
that kind of courage in me.

00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:02.741 position:50% align:center
[MAYA cries]

00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:04.784 position:50% align:center
[MAYA] I was so scared
I would lose you both,

00:13:04.868 --> 00:13:06.745 position:50% align:center
and I just...

00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:21.509 position:50% align:center
[singing in Spanish]

00:13:27.098 --> 00:13:28.516 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
Damn it!

00:13:28.600 --> 00:13:30.769 position:50% align:center
'Kay. All set!

00:13:38.401 --> 00:13:41.529 position:50% align:center
[CROWD]
Joe! Joe! Joe!

00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:46.076 position:50% align:center
--Here.
--Great. Thanks, babe.

00:13:49.954 --> 00:13:51.373 position:50% align:center
Good to go?

00:13:54.167 --> 00:13:54.918 position:50% align:center
[MIGUEL]
Daddy!

00:13:55.001 --> 00:13:56.252 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
Hey, bud!

00:13:56.336 --> 00:13:59.005 position:50% align:center
[DOCTOR A] A transplant is
the only option we have.

00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:04.636 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:14:04.719 --> 00:14:05.595 position:50% align:center
Shit!

00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:06.554 position:50% align:center
[REPORTER A]
We're live...!

00:14:06.638 --> 00:14:07.681 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN A]
My kids are inside!

00:14:07.764 --> 00:14:09.182 position:50% align:center
Wait, Mac!

00:14:15.021 --> 00:14:15.897 position:50% align:center
[BOY A, GIRL A crying]

00:14:15.980 --> 00:14:18.441 position:50% align:center
Come on!

00:14:18.525 --> 00:14:20.568 position:50% align:center
[BOY A]
Mommy!

00:14:20.652 --> 00:14:22.946 position:50% align:center
[COP A]
Whoa, Mac! You all right?

00:14:25.323 --> 00:14:26.950 position:50% align:center
[MAYA]
Mac!

00:14:30.537 --> 00:14:31.538 position:50% align:center
[MIGUEL]
Daddy!

00:14:31.621 --> 00:14:34.207 position:50% align:center
[chuckling]

00:14:35.917 --> 00:14:37.794 position:50% align:center
[MAC chuckles]

00:14:39.004 --> 00:14:41.715 position:50% align:center
[CROWD cheering]

00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:43.842 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:14:43.925 --> 00:14:48.930 position:50% align:center
[BOTH laughing]

00:14:56.271 --> 00:14:59.607 position:50% align:center
Courage? That's not what it was.

00:15:02.527 --> 00:15:03.945 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
I was so terrified.

00:15:04.029 --> 00:15:07.282 position:50% align:center
I thought everything I cared
about was gonna disappear.

00:15:10.285 --> 00:15:13.163 position:50% align:center
Wait, Mac. Where're you off to?

00:15:15.457 --> 00:15:17.625 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna head home.

00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:23.798 position:50% align:center
[speaking Spanish]

00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:31.181 position:50% align:center
[MAC singing]

00:15:31.264 --> 00:15:32.849 position:50% align:center
[MAC] "As the Nomad
buried the hummingbird

00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:34.476 position:50% align:center
on the side of the road,

00:15:34.559 --> 00:15:38.772 position:50% align:center
he began singing its song,
as if to mourn its loss.

00:15:38.855 --> 00:15:41.900 position:50% align:center
And he found the song
eased his weary soul,

00:15:41.983 --> 00:15:43.568 position:50% align:center
so much that he
carried on singing

00:15:43.651 --> 00:15:46.237 position:50% align:center
as he continued his journey.

00:15:46.321 --> 00:15:51.785 position:50% align:center
Till at last, he found himself
looking out over the ocean.

00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:55.163 position:50% align:center
As the stars shimmered on
the still surface of the sea,

00:15:55.246 --> 00:15:56.956 position:50% align:center
the Nomad spoke.

00:15:57.040 --> 00:15:58.625 position:50% align:center
'I am a nomad who walked

00:15:58.708 --> 00:16:01.461 position:50% align:center
a long and winding
road to reach you.

00:16:01.544 --> 00:16:06.007 position:50% align:center
Now, Ocean, at journey's end,
will you grant my wish?'

00:16:06.091 --> 00:16:10.178 position:50% align:center
A tiny wave carried the
ocean's reply to the shore.

00:16:10.261 --> 00:16:12.514 position:50% align:center
'Countless travelers
have come before you,

00:16:12.597 --> 00:16:15.975 position:50% align:center
all to wish for money,
fame, or death.

00:16:16.059 --> 00:16:19.062 position:50% align:center
Which of these is your desire?'

00:16:19.145 --> 00:16:20.730 position:50% align:center
As the Nomad responded,

00:16:20.814 --> 00:16:23.858 position:50% align:center
his once-tired eyes
beamed with light.

00:16:23.942 --> 00:16:26.986 position:50% align:center
'I've already had everything
this life has to offer.

00:16:27.070 --> 00:16:31.157 position:50% align:center
My wish is not for
any of those things.

00:16:31.241 --> 00:16:33.618 position:50% align:center
I desire one thing only.

00:16:33.702 --> 00:16:37.706 position:50% align:center
Please, show me the
way back home.'"

00:16:41.668 --> 00:16:42.711 position:50% align:center
Then what happened?

00:16:42.794 --> 00:16:44.963 position:50% align:center
Did the Nomad ever
make it home? Huh?

00:16:45.046 --> 00:16:47.173 position:50% align:center
His heart will always
know the way,

00:16:47.257 --> 00:16:49.884 position:50% align:center
no matter how far he goes.

00:16:49.968 --> 00:16:52.804 position:50% align:center
So I know he'll get
there in the end.

00:16:56.099 --> 00:17:00.103 position:50% align:center
[engine humming]

00:17:07.861 --> 00:17:09.571 position:50% align:center
You're home.

00:17:13.700 --> 00:17:15.869 position:50% align:center
[MAYA] I didn't know if you
were going to come back!

00:17:15.952 --> 00:17:18.079 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry to make
you worry about me.

00:17:18.163 --> 00:17:21.082 position:50% align:center
It's my fault.
I made this happen.

00:17:21.166 --> 00:17:23.585 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
That's not true.

00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:26.087 position:50% align:center
If I were the one who had
to choose back then,

00:17:26.171 --> 00:17:28.548 position:50% align:center
I would've done the same thing.

00:17:28.631 --> 00:17:30.467 position:50% align:center
Thank you for saving
Miguel's life,

00:17:30.550 --> 00:17:31.760 position:50% align:center
and for making a tough call

00:17:31.843 --> 00:17:34.304 position:50% align:center
when I couldn't be
there to help you.

00:17:36.014 --> 00:17:37.807 position:50% align:center
There's somethin' Grandma
always used to tell me

00:17:37.891 --> 00:17:39.434 position:50% align:center
when I was a kid:

00:17:39.517 --> 00:17:43.188 position:50% align:center
"Bad things happen now so good
things can happen later."

00:17:44.856 --> 00:17:48.318 position:50% align:center
Right now, I have
everything that matters.

00:17:49.611 --> 00:17:53.031 position:50% align:center
Daddy!

00:17:53.114 --> 00:17:54.407 position:50% align:center
Welcome home, Daddy!

00:17:54.491 --> 00:17:55.116 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
Hi, Miguel.

00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:57.869 position:50% align:center
Mommy. He came back.

00:18:00.538 --> 00:18:02.457 position:50% align:center
Here.

00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:03.958 position:50% align:center
Sorry I scared you.

00:18:04.042 --> 00:18:06.920 position:50% align:center
[MIGUEL] Ha! Your face is
all hairy! It looks so weird!

00:18:07.003 --> 00:18:09.839 position:50% align:center
[ALL laughing]

00:18:09.923 --> 00:18:11.758 position:50% align:center
[MAC]
If we're gonna move forward,

00:18:11.841 --> 00:18:14.469 position:50% align:center
there's one more
thing I have to do.

00:18:44.249 --> 00:18:45.500 position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:18:45.583 --> 00:18:48.878 position:50% align:center
<i>Â¡Que pasa!</i>
Looks like Mac's back!

00:18:48.962 --> 00:18:51.339 position:50% align:center
I came to tell you
that I'm done.

00:18:51.756 --> 00:18:53.091 position:50% align:center
[SAKUMA]
Huh?

00:18:53.174 --> 00:18:56.761 position:50% align:center
I'm having the fight with Joe,
but I'm doing it my way.

00:18:56.845 --> 00:18:59.514 position:50% align:center
My training with ROSCO is over.

00:19:00.932 --> 00:19:02.434 position:50% align:center
Which way would that be?

00:19:02.517 --> 00:19:05.729 position:50% align:center
I'll keep playing your mascot
till we're done with the match,

00:19:05.812 --> 00:19:07.981 position:50% align:center
then we put all this behind us.

00:19:08.064 --> 00:19:09.607 position:50% align:center
Yeah, fine.

00:19:09.691 --> 00:19:12.944 position:50% align:center
Not a huge surprise that this
is where everything ended up.

00:19:13.028 --> 00:19:15.196 position:50% align:center
Suit yourself, bud.

00:19:15.280 --> 00:19:19.951 position:50% align:center
I can't complain.
I got all I could out of you.

00:19:20.035 --> 00:19:21.286 position:50% align:center
One thing.

00:19:21.369 --> 00:19:23.747 position:50% align:center
You know I'm still gonna
need you to win the fight.

00:19:23.830 --> 00:19:25.582 position:50% align:center
Even if you've decided
you're done,

00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:29.377 position:50% align:center
don't go dragging down ROSCO's
brand on your way out.

00:19:29.461 --> 00:19:32.088 position:50% align:center
Adios, amigo!

00:19:36.176 --> 00:19:39.179 position:50% align:center
[HAKEEM] Keep pushin'!
You don't have time to rest!

00:19:40.764 --> 00:19:42.474 position:50% align:center
Why aren't you moving
your feet, Mac?

00:19:42.557 --> 00:19:46.478 position:50% align:center
[yelling]

00:19:52.317 --> 00:19:53.902 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
Do you remember?

00:19:53.985 --> 00:19:56.696 position:50% align:center
We had a conversation
right here once.

00:19:56.780 --> 00:19:58.948 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
Yeah, I think I do.

00:19:59.032 --> 00:20:01.993 position:50% align:center
About a young boxer
with a lot of potential.

00:20:02.077 --> 00:20:04.371 position:50% align:center
The first time I heard of Liu.

00:20:04.454 --> 00:20:06.122 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
That's right.

00:20:06.206 --> 00:20:07.540 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
How's he been?

00:20:07.624 --> 00:20:09.751 position:50% align:center
[YURI]
Getting ready to start PT.

00:20:09.834 --> 00:20:12.587 position:50% align:center
He never even thought
about giving up.

00:20:15.215 --> 00:20:16.966 position:50% align:center
I see.

00:20:19.427 --> 00:20:21.221 position:50% align:center
Now we're having
another conversation

00:20:21.304 --> 00:20:23.098 position:50% align:center
in the exact same place.

00:20:23.181 --> 00:20:25.141 position:50% align:center
Who would've guessed?

00:20:25.225 --> 00:20:26.935 position:50% align:center
I'm the one they call
the Raging Bull!

00:20:27.018 --> 00:20:30.313 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna break off your horns
and call you beef curry!

00:20:30.397 --> 00:20:33.900 position:50% align:center
[SANTA]
Say your prayers, matador!

00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:36.486 position:50% align:center
The light you showed us is here.

00:20:36.569 --> 00:20:37.654 position:50% align:center
[SACHIO]
Get back here!

00:20:37.737 --> 00:20:41.116 position:50% align:center
[YURI] I don't plan
on worrying anymore.

00:20:41.199 --> 00:20:45.370 position:50% align:center
So, Joe, don't die. Okay?

00:20:47.330 --> 00:20:49.582 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:20:49.666 --> 00:20:54.212 position:50% align:center
[BONJIRI] Hey! It's chowtime,
so come dig in, guys!

00:20:54.295 --> 00:20:55.922 position:50% align:center
[OICHO]
You heard him, let's eat!

00:20:56.006 --> 00:20:57.382 position:50% align:center
[JOE]
Right.

00:21:10.395 --> 00:21:14.399 position:50% align:center
[CROWD chattering]

00:21:19.612 --> 00:21:22.407 position:50% align:center
Hey, Miguel.

00:21:22.490 --> 00:21:24.409 position:50% align:center
This is your dad's
biggest fight,

00:21:24.492 --> 00:21:26.619 position:50% align:center
so keep your eyes on me.

00:21:29.414 --> 00:21:33.877 position:50% align:center
No need to worry, Mac.
We're with you all the way.

00:21:39.924 --> 00:21:42.260 position:50% align:center
Can't believe it's still here.

00:21:43.636 --> 00:21:46.431 position:50% align:center
This is it, Pops. Watch us.

00:21:47.390 --> 00:21:50.060 position:50% align:center
[ARAGAKI]
It's time, Sachio.

00:21:50.143 --> 00:21:51.478 position:50% align:center
[SACHIO]
Right.

00:21:53.688 --> 00:21:58.693 position:50% align:center
[SAKUMA humming]

00:22:01.946 --> 00:22:03.448 position:50% align:center
Hold on.

00:22:06.451 --> 00:22:08.036 position:50% align:center
You came after all.

00:22:08.119 --> 00:22:13.124 position:50% align:center
[CROWD shouting]